RACE.RACE_TEXT: Aqueduct Turf Sprint Championship S. AQUEDUCT RACE 9 6F Outer turf CR: 102. Stakes Purse 150000. OUTER TURF FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NOTHING BETTER went to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, vied inside on the turn, responded well when asked near the quarter-pole then came under a drive in upper stretch and held under steady urging. BOAT'S A ROCKIN was rated just off the pace, drafted inside on the turn, was asked near the quarter-pole then came off the rail into upper stretch, pursued the winner while remaining on his inside lead in the drive and was second best. ALOGON settled under some restraint, raced inside for most of the turn then shifted to the two path, moved out while asked for his best outside the furlong marker and finished willingly for the show. OUR SHOT dropped back then was coaxed along off the pace, went around the turn in the two path, came four wide into the stretch and lacked the needed kick then just missed the show. WITTY brushed with a foe after the start, settled near the back, saved ground on the turn, cut the corner into the stretch and lacked the needed response. DANCING BUCK stalked the pace on the outside, made a bid with three furlongs to run, vied in the two path on the turn, chased under a drive into the final furlong and weakened. FORE HARP brushed with a foe after the start, tracked the pace on the outside, chased three wide on the turn and came up empty. THIN WHITE DUKE settled towards the rear, was roused four wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. VACATION DANCE settled in the middle of the field, went around the turn in the two path and failed to respond. RUN CURTIS RUN hit the outside of the gate and was off slow, spotted the front a few lengths, settled on the outside, went five wide on the turn, came six wide into the stretch and was no factor. GRATEFUL BRED settled off the pace, went three wide on the turn, came four wide into the stretch and failed to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 10 6F Dirt CR: 80. Starter Allowance Purse 55000. (UP TO $9,570 NYSBFOA) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN OR CLAIMING. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROUD FOOT dueled five paths off the inside down the backstretch and then three wide through the turn with SHAMAN PRINCESS to her inside, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and swung three wide into upper stretch, edged clear under a drive to prevail. ICY REPLY chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung three wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild kick to just get up for the place honors over a rival on the wire. SHE'S AWESOME chased four then two wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung five wide into upper stretch, offered up a mild kick and just missed for the place honors. WILL BE FAMOUS seven paths off the inside down the backstretch, went five wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung five wide into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. SHAMAN PRINCESS dueled from the four path and then then two wide through the turn with PROUD FOOT to her outside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, ran on prominent to the eighth pole, then weakened in the late going. MERAVIGLIOSO chased five then four wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, swung six wide into upper stretch, offered no rally. MY GIRL JAL chased six paths off the inside down the backstretch and then four wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, went seven wide into upper stretch and tired. SPUN SPECIAL stumbled at the start, chased four then three wide under coaxing from the three-eighths, cornered four wide into upper stretch and tired. BELLA PRINCIPESSA got bumped solidly at the start by BOSS LADY KIM, chased along the inside under a ride from midway on the turn, spun two to three wide into upper stretch and made no impact. BOSS LADY KIM broke out at the start bumping the aforementioned foe, chased just off the inside and then along the inside under coaxing from three furlongs out, took the inside route into upper stretch and tired.
